The likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper are: cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.SE. 

Reasoning: The paper discusses a software framework for building question-answering systems, which is relevant to several sub-fields of computer science. cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as it deals with natural language processing and understanding, which is a key component of question-answering systems. cs.IR (Information Retrieval), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.LG (Machine Learning) are also likely categories as they are related to the development of intelligent systems that can process and analyze large amounts of data to provide answers to questions. Finally, cs.SE (Software Engineering) is a possible category as the paper discusses the development of a software framework for building QA systems.
